<P>NARRATIVE, of a five years' expedition against the <HI>Revolted Negroes</HI> of <HI>Surinam,</HI> in GUIANA, on the WILD COAST of SOUTH AMERICA; from the year 1772, to 1777: elucidating the History of that Country and describing its Productions. <HI>Viz.</HI> Quadrupedes, Birds, Fishes, Reptiles, Trees, Shrubs, Fruits, &amp; Roots; with an account of the INDIANS of Guiana, &amp; NEGROES of Guinea.</P>
<P>By <HI>CAPT^N. J. G. STEDMAN.</HI> illustrated with 80 elegant Engravings from drawings made by the Author.</P>
