<P>For a fuller botanical de&s;cription than either my know|ledge or my limits will allow, I refer the reader to the ingenious Dr. Bancroft, who&s;e merit in this particular is perhaps known by few, but who claims every atten|tion from having lived &s;o long in Demerary; and to whom the thanks of the world in general are due, for his inge|nious "Letters to Dr. Pitcairn, F. R. C. P. &amp;c." publi&s;hed in 1766.</P>
